        "client_msg_id": "1c83b05c-edfc-405a-ae5d-d5d210c99dfb",
        "text": "Hi everyone! I’m Peter and I’ve been noodling with technology since my parents got a Mac Plus in 1984 and I started making little games in Quick Basic. This has morphed into 1 year of a computer science degree which then became an architecture degree (as in buildings, not software), and a career doing web development and more recently agile coaching, portfolio management, digital transformation and DevOpsy stuff.\n\nGenerally I love helping digital teams to get clear on what they’re doing and why and then get better at doing those things while having more fun.\n\nRecently I’ve been delighted to discover <https:\/\/nudel.cc\/|Nudel> and <https:\/\/www.pastagang.cc\/|Pastagang> and all the things that go with it!\n\nProfessionally you can learn more about me <https:\/\/www.peterkappus.com\/?utm_source=foc_slack|here>. Creatively, I post algorithmic art and other things as “<https:\/\/www.abstraktor.com\/|Abstraktor>” and I perennially debate how to attract mainstream clients while also sharing my more niche passions and experiments under the same “brand”.\n\nExcited to meet you all!",
